{ This is the other exception. With White's king unable to participate, there's a second stalemate motif that saves Black in the event of a bishop's pawn. }
1. Qb3+ Ka1! { And already we see the point - Qxc2 stalemates again. Any check will force ...Kb1 and we'd be back to essentially the initial position, and any king move allows promotion. } { [%cal Gb3c2] } (1... Kc1 { also draws, but just wastes time using the same motif as in the main line, e.g. } 2. Kg7 Kd2 3. Qb4+ Kd1 4. Qd4+ Kc1 5. Qc3 Kb1 6. Qb3+ Ka1!) 2. Qxc2 $10 { And stalemate. } *


