{ Here White wins, as the king is in the winning zone and it's his/her turn to move. In short, either the king gets to b3 in two moves and mates Black with a pretty zugzwang, or a king supports Qc2# - generously made possible by a queen promotion on a1 removing the Black king's flight square. } { [%csl Ge1,Ge2,Ge3,Ge4,Gd4,Gc5,Gd5,Gb5,Ga5,Yb3,Yd3,Yd2,Yd1] }
1. Qb3+ Ka1 2. Qd1+ Kb2 3. Qd2+ { [%csl Ga5,Gb5,Gc5,Gd5,Gd4,Re5][%cal Ga5b3] } 3... Kb1 (3... Kb3 4. Qc1 { [%cal Gc1a1] }) 4. Kb4 a1=Q 5. Kb3 $18 { [%cal Gd2d1,Gc2b2] } 5... Qf6 (5... Qa6 6. Qb2#) 6. Qd1# *


