1. g4 { The Grob - a very weak move that endangers both White's kingside and g-pawn with the hopes of some cheap tricks. } { [%csl Rg4,Re1][%cal Yg4g3] } 1... d5 { The most principled move, threatening g4 immediately and blunting the g2-bishop. } 2. Bg2 (2. h3 h5! { is covered in chapter 2. }) 2... Bxg4 3. c4 { [%cal Yg2b7] } 3... c6 { The main topic of chapter 3. } 4. cxd5 (4. Qb3 { is likely to transpose, but has some independent flavor as well. }) 4... cxd5 5. Qb3 { [%cal Yb3b7,Yg2d5] } 5... Nf6 6. Nc3 e6 7. Qxb7 { [%csl Yb7] } 7... Nbd7 *


