[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/TonyRo"]
[UTCDate "2017.01.24"]
[UTCTime "22:34:08"]

1. d4 e6 2. c4 d5 3. g3 { This move order is also popular due to it's recommendation in Boris Avrukh's "GM Repertoire" series. For the most part it should transpose back to Chapters 1 & 2. } 3... Nf6 4. Bg2 (4. Nf3) 4... Bb4+ 5. Nd2 { This seems to be the only move that really presents White with independent options, and it's not particularly popular. } (5. Bd2 Bd6 6. Nf3 { White has little better than simply transposing back to Chapter 2. }) (5. Nc3 O-O 6. Nf3 dxc4 { and we've transposed back to Chapter 1. }) 5... O-O (5... dxc4 6. Qa4+) 6. Nf3 dxc4 7. Qc2 (7. O-O b5 { transposes back to Chapter 1. }) *


