1. Nf3 (1. f4 e5 2. fxe5 d6 { The Litisin Gambit (2.e4!?) and 2.d3!? resemble and borrow ideas from the From Gambit. }) 1... f5 (1... d6 2. d4 f5) 2. g3 (2. d3!? { Popular and thought to be strong for a while, but easy to move-order your way out of as Black with 1...d6 or 1...e6. } 2... Nc6! (2... Nf6 3. e4 fxe4 4. Ng5 (4. dxe4 Nxe4 5. Bd3 Nf6 6. Ng5)) 3. d4!? e6 4. c4 Nf6 { This is the accepted theoretical solution to 2.d3. }) (2. e4 { The Litisin Gambit. } 2... fxe4 3. Ng5 Nf6 4. d3 exd3 5. Bxd3 $40 g6 6. Nxh7! Rxh7 (6... Nxh7 7. Bxg6#) 7. Bxg6+ Rf7 $16) 2... Nf6 3. Bg2 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. d4 O-O 6. b4!? d6 7. c4 (7. Bb2 { This is more popular. } 7... Nc6!? 8. b5 Na5 9. Nbd2 a6! 10. a4 Bd7 11. c4 c6! $132) 7... Ne4!? 8. Bb2 (8. Qb3!?) 8... c5!? 9. a3 (9. Nbd2!? cxb4 (9... Nxd2 10. Qxd2 cxb4 11. Qxb4 Nc6 12. Qd2 e5! $132) 10. Nxe4 fxe4 11. Ng5 $14) 9... cxb4?! 10. axb4 Qc7?! { [%csl Rc7] } 11. Qb3 Be6?! 12. d5 Bf7 { [%csl Re6,Gd5][%cal Gb2g7] } 13. Bxg7 Kxg7 14. Nc3 $16 Nd7? (14... Nxc3 { This was probably the better option for Black, avoiding the weak e4-pawn. But it's still quite unpleasant! } 15. Qxc3+ Kg8 16. Nd4 $16) 15. Nxe4 fxe4 16. Ng5 Nf6 (16... Ne5 17. Rfc1 Rfc8 18. c5 $18) 17. Nxe4 Nxe4 18. Bxe4 e6 19. Rfd1 (19. dxe6!? Bxe6 20. Qe3 $18) 19... Qe7 20. dxe6 Qxe6 21. Bxb7 Rad8 22. Qb2+ (22. Rxa7 Qxe2 23. Bd5 Kg8 24. Rxf7 Rxf7 25. Bxf7+ Kxf7 26. c5+ $18) 22... Kg8 23. Bd5 Qf5 (23... Qe7! 24. Qd4 Bxd5 25. Qxd5+ Rf7 26. e3 $18) 24. Qd4 (24. Rxa7! Bxd5 (24... Rd7 25. Rxd7 Qxd7 26. Qd4 $18)) 24... Rde8 25. Rxa7 Rxe2 26. Bxf7+ Rxf7 27. Ra8+ Rf8 28. Qd5+ Kg7 (28... Qxd5 29. Rxf8+ Kxf8 30. Rxd5 Ke7 $18) 29. Ra7+ Rf7 30. Rxf7+ Qxf7 31. Qxf7+ Kxf7 32. Rxd6 1-0


