1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 g6 4. c4 (4. d4 Bg7 5. O-O O-O 6. c4 { [%cal Gc7c6,Gd5c4] }) 4... c6 5. b3 (5. O-O Bg7 6. d4 O-O) 5... Bg7 6. Bb2 O-O 7. O-O { Now Black has a lot of choices: } 7... a5!? (7... Bg4 8. d3 Nbd7 9. Nbd2 Re8 10. h3 Bxf3 11. Nxf3 e5 12. cxd5 cxd5 13. Rc1 $14 { Pantsulaia, Levan - Baramidze, David, 1-0, EU-chT (Men) 19th, 2013, https://lichess.org/veJV5q9J }) (7... Nbd7 8. Qc2 (8. d4!? $14) 8... Re8 9. Nc3 (9. d4!? Ne4 10. e3 $14 { Badea, Bela - Teodorescu, Ioan, 1-0, ROM-chT, 2008, https://lichess.org/nmB68ntn }) 9... e5 (9... dxc4 10. bxc4 e5 11. d3 Nc5 12. Rfd1 { Speelman, Jonathan S - Proehl, Holger, 1/2-1/2, Bundesliga 9899, 1999, https://lichess.org/V2G7JltK }) 10. cxd5 Nxd5 11. d3 $13 { Stocek, Jiri - Arngrimsson, Dagur, 1-0, EU-Cup 25th, 2009, https://lichess.org/AGgT4lNf }) 8. Nc3 (8. d3 Na6 (8... a4 9. Nbd2 axb3 10. axb3 Rxa1 11. Qxa1 $14 { Psakhis, Lev - Svidler, Peter, 1-0, Wydra Memorial rapidplay, 2000, https://lichess.org/PxAZLnxK } { [%csl Ga1][%cal Ga1a8,Ga1g7] }) 9. Nbd2 a4 10. Qc1!? Bg4 11. Re1 Re8 12. Ne5 $14 { Malakhov, V. - Olafsson, H1., 1-0, World Blitz 2015, https://lichess.org/ikUaU782 }) 8... Ne4 9. Na4! (9. d4 Nxc3 10. Bxc3 $14 Bf5 (10... Nd7)) 9... Bxb2 10. Nxb2 { [%csl Ya5,Ye4] } 10... Nd7?! (10... Na6 11. d3 Nf6 12. d4 Bf5 13. Ne5 Nc7 14. Na4 h5 15. Rc1 $14 { Baramidze, David - L'Ami, Erwin, 1/2-1/2, Bundesliga 1011, 2011, https://lichess.org/GLQ8LtIa }) (10... d4!? $13 $146 { [%cal Yd2d3,Ye4c3] }) 11. d3 (11. d4 Ndf6 12. Nd3 $13 { [%cal Gc8f5,Gf5g4] }) 11... Nef6 { [%csl Yd7,Yf6] } 12. d4 $14 { [%csl Gd3,Gf3,Ya8,Yc8][%cal Re7e5,Gb2d3] } 12... b6 13. Rc1 (13. Nd3 { straight away is also totally reasonable. }) 13... Bb7 14. Nd3 Rc8 15. Nfe5 (15. e3!?) 15... Nxe5 16. dxe5!? (16. Nxe5 Nd7 (16... c5 17. cxd5 Bxd5 18. dxc5 Bxg2 19. Kxg2 Rxc5 20. Rxc5 bxc5 21. Qxd8 Rxd8 22. Nd3 $16 { [%csl Ya5,Yc5] }) 17. Qd3 { Cummings } (17. Nd3 e6 18. e3 $14)) 16... Nd7 { [%csl Ge5] } 17. Qd2!? (17. e6!? fxe6 18. Bh3 $36 { [%csl Re6][%cal Gd1d2,Gd3f4] }) (17. Qc2 e6 18. Rfd1 Qc7 19. f4 $14) 17... dxc4! { Black goes for it. } 18. Rxc4 Nxe5 19. Rh4 h5 $7 (19... Nxd3?? 20. Qh6 { and White mates in two. }) 20. Rd1 Nxd3 21. Qh6 Qd6 (21... e6 22. Rxh5! gxh5 23. Be4 f5 24. Qg6+ $10 { [%cal Gg6h6] }) 22. Rxd3 Qf6 23. Be4 Ba6 24. Re3 (24. Rf3?? Qa1+ 25. Kg2 Bxe2 $19 { [%cal Ra1f1] }) 24... Qg7 (24... Rfd8!? 25. Rxh5 Qg7 26. Qxg7+ Kxg7 27. Re5 Rd1+ 28. Kg2 e6 $17 { [%csl Ye5,Ye4,Ye3] }) 25. Qg5 Rcd8 (25... e6 { might have been more stubborn. }) 26. Qxe7 Rd1+ 27. Kg2 Qa1 28. Bxc6 { And odd shift in the dynamics compared with the position just 8 moves ago - it's White who's up a pawn, and it's White who has the king in trouble! } 28... Rg1+ 29. Kf3 Qf1? { [%cal Rf1g2,Rg2c6] } (29... Rf1! { [%cal Gf3f4] } 30. Kf4? Rxf2+ 31. Kg5?? (31. Bf3) 31... Rf5+ 32. Kh6 Qg7#) 30. Kf4! { [%cal Gf4g5,Gg5h6] } 30... Qxf2+?? (30... Qa1! 31. Kg5 Rc1 32. Bd5 $13) 31. Kg5 Kg7 (31... Qf5+ 32. Kh6 Rc1 33. Qxf8+ Kxf8 34. Re8# { [%cal Gh6g7] }) 32. Rf4 Qxh2 33. Qf6+ Kh7 34. Qxg6+! Kh8 (34... fxg6 35. Re7+ Kg8 36. Bd5+ Rf7 37. Re8+ Kg7 38. Rxf7#) 35. Kh6! { 1-0 Black resigns. } 1-0


