[ChapterName "An Actual Refutation"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/xqVf4n36/OKXgVUdq"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Nxe5 Nxe5? 5. d4 Ng6 6. e5 (6. Bc4? Bb4! 7. e5 d5! 8. exf6 dxc4 9. fxg7 Bxc3+ 10. bxc3 Rg8 11. O-O (11. Qe2+ Qe7 12. Be3 Be6 $19) 11... Be6 12. Qh5 Qd5 13. Qxh7 O-O-O $19) 6... Ng8 { Black decides to try and keep everything and accept a bit of discomfort. } 7. Bc4 (7. Qf3 { has also been played a bit, but should transpose after } 7... c6 (7... d5!? { also seems quite good, Qxd5 would trade queens a piece down and } 8. Nxd5 c6 { is awful for White after ...Qxd4 next. }) 8. Bc4 (8. h4 d5 9. h5 Nh4 $19) 8... d5 { , etc. }) 7... c6! { A relatively rare move, though not a novelty. } { [%cal Gd1e2] } (7... d5!? { also seems very good. Just like in many other gambits, Black can return a pawn or two and still be for choice because White's material investment was so high to begin with. } 8. Nxd5?! (8. Bxd5 N8e7 9. Bg5!? (9. Bb3 Nf5 10. Be3 Bb4 $19) 9... c6 10. Bb3 h6 11. Be3 Nf5 12. O-O h5! $19) 8... Be6 9. Ne3 (9. Qf3 c6 10. Ne3 Qxd4 $19) 9... Bxc4 10. Nxc4 Qd5 11. Ne3 Qc6 $19) 8. Qe2 { B.Go - R.Hoffman, Hoogeveen 2011 - In my opinion the trickiest move to face, as Black needs to know a few concrete ideas. } (8. O-O d5! 9. exd6 (9. Bd3 N8e7 10. Qh5 Qd7! 11. f4 Nf5! $19 12. Ne2 Nge7 13. g4 g6 14. Qh3 Ng7 $19) 9... Bxd6 10. Re1+ N8e7 { [%cal Ge8g8] } 11. d5 O-O) (8. Qf3 d5! 9. exd6 (9. Bd3 Be6 10. O-O Qd7 $19) 9... Be6 10. d5 (10. Bxe6 fxe6 $19) 10... Ne5 11. Qe2 Nxc4 12. dxe6 Nxd6 13. exf7+ Kxf7 { [%cal Gg8f6] } 14. Be3 Nf6 15. O-O-O { G.Jung - N.Heldt, Bremen 2014 } { [%cal Gd8a5,Gd8e7] } 15... Qe7! $19 (15... Be7? 16. Bf4! Re8 17. Qd3! $40) (15... Qa5 $19)) 8... Bb4! $146 9. O-O (9. Bxf7+ Kxf7 10. Qc4+ d5 11. exd6+ Be6 { [%csl Ge6] } 12. Qxb4 Qb6 $19) 9... d5! (9... Bxc3!? 10. bxc3 N8e7 11. f4 O-O 12. f5 Nxf5! 13. Rxf5 d5 14. Bd3 Bxf5 15. Bxf5 $17) 10. exd6+ Kf8 { [%cal Gc3e4] } 11. Bxf7 { White has this resource at various spots in this line, but in a lot of cases it just simplifies and helps Black unravel. } (11. d5 cxd5 12. Nxd5 { [%csl Gb4] } 12... Bxd6 13. Be3 Be6 14. Rad1 Qc8 $19 { [%cal Ge6g4,Bg8e7] }) (11. Ne4 Nf6 (11... Bxd6 $19) 12. Bg5 Bxd6 13. Nxf6 (13. Bxf6 gxf6 $19 { [%cal Gf8g7] }) 13... Be7! $19 (13... gxf6 14. Bh6+ Kg8 15. Rfe1 { [%cal Rc4f7,Ye2c4] } 15... Nf8 16. Qh5 $40)) 11... Bxc3 12. Bxg8 Kxg8 13. Qc4+ (13. bxc3 Qxd6 14. f4 Qe6! 15. Qf3 Qf5! $19) 13... Kf8 14. bxc3 Qxd6 15. Re1 Qd5 16. Qb4+ Kf7 17. c4 Qd8 18. Ba3 b6 $19 *


