[FEN "r7/6p1/1Pk2p1p/2p1pP2/2Pb2P1/1R3K1P/3B4/8 w - - 0 43"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2017.08.13"]
[UTCTime "22:50:03"]

{ A.Czebe-P.Prohaszka, Budapest 2007 }
43. b7! Rb8 44. Ba5! { The only sequence that wins - Black can't stop White from getting his bishop to f8. } 44... Rxb7 45. Rxb7 Kxb7 { Black is actually up a pawn, but with all of his pawns on the same color as the bishops and with White having easy access to the base of the chain, he's already lost. } { [%cal Ya5d8,Rb7c8] } 46. Bd8! { [%csl Gg7,Gf6,Ge5,Gh6,Gc5][%cal Gd8e7,Ge7f8] } 46... Bc3 47. Be7 Kc6 48. Bf8 Bd2 49. Bxg7 Bg5 { White has won his pawn back and Black still has the issue of all his pawns sitting on dark squares, but how does White make progress with the dark-squared bishop holding everything together from g5? } 50. Bf8!! { White takes the long road back to prepare h4! } { [%cal Gf8e7,Ge7d8,Gd8a5,Ga5e1,Be1h4,Bh3h4] } (50. Kg3?! Bf4+ 51. Kf3 Bg5 { does not make any progress. }) 50... Kb6 51. Be7 Kc6 52. Bd8 Kd6 53. Ba5 Kc6 54. Be1! { [%cal Gh3h4,Bg5f6,Bg5h6] } 54... Kd6 55. h4 Bf4 56. Ba5! { And now the same maneuver wins again! } 56... Kd7 57. Bb6 Kc6 58. Bd8 { 1-0 Black resigns } *


