[UTCTime "23:00:30"]

{ L.Polugaevsky-H.Mecking, Mar del Plata 1971 }
38. Kc3! { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gc3d4] } 38... Bf3 39. Kd4 Bg2 40. h4! Bf3 41. b4 { The status of both players pawns is placed in the starkest contrast. } 41... Bh1 42. Be2! { [%cal Ge2g4,Gg4c8] } 42... Bg2 43. Bg4 Be4 44. Bc8 Kc7 45. Be6 Kd6 46. Bg8 h6 47. Bf7! { Black's king and bishop both have to protect two squares and can't move. His only choice is to push the last pawn on to a light square and fix his kingside weakness in place. } { [%cal Be4d5,Be4g6,Bd6c5,Bd6e5] } 47... h5 48. Be8 Bc2 49. Bf7 Be4 50. f5! Bxf5 (50... gxf5 51. Bxh5 $18 { [%csl Gh4][%cal Gh4h8] }) 51. Bxd5 { [%csl Gb7][%cal Ge3e8] } 51... Bc8 52. e4 $22 Ke7 53. Ke5 $22 { [%csl Ge5,Re7] } 53... g5 (53... Kf8 54. Kf6 $18) 54. hxg5 h4 55. g6 h3 (55... Kf8 56. Kf6 h3 57. g7+ Ke8 58. g8=Q+ $18) 56. g7 h2 57. g8=Q h1=Q 58. Qf7+ Kd8 59. Qf8+ { and Black resigned, since it's mate in 2 with: } 59... Kd7 60. Be6+ Kc6 61. Qc5# *


