{ A.Wojtkiewicz-A.Khalifman, Keres Memorial Rakvere 1993 }
30. a4!? g5? $18 (30... Bd7! 31. b3 Kc5 32. Bf3 { [%csl Ga4][%cal Gf3d1,Gb3b4] } 32... Be8 33. b4+ Kd6 34. Bd1 Bg6 { [%cal Rg6e4] } 35. f5 Be8 { [%cal Rd6e5] } 36. Kd4 g6! 37. fxg6 Bxg6 38. Bf3 Be8 39. b5 (39. Bxd5 Bxa4 40. Bxb7 { allows White to fight on for a bit, but this is a draw after } 40... Bb5) 39... Bf7 40. Bd1 Bg6! 41. Bb3 Be4 $10) 31. Kd4 Bf7 32. Bf3 Be6 33. f5! Bf7 34. b4! Be8 35. b5! { [%cal Re8c6] } 35... Bf7 36. Bd1! Bg8 37. Bb3 $22 Bf7 38. e4 { [%cal Gb3f7] } 38... Bg8 39. Ba2 Bf7 40. Bxd5 Bxd5 41. exd5 Kc7 42. Kc3 Kd6 43. Kc4 Ke5 44. a5! { [%cal Ga5a6] } 44... bxa5 45. Kc5 { [%cal Gd5d6] } 45... a4 46. d6 b6+ 47. Kc6 a3 48. d7 a2 49. d8=Q a1=Q 50. Qd6+ Ke4 51. Kxb6 $18 { and White won in 10 more moves. } *


